    {
      "kind": "working_space_divergence_refines_rule",
      "summary": "PAELevels Black/White In remap DIVERGES (72 lvl): FCP's endpoint stretch is GENTLER than TS. whiteIn=0.7 in=64 -> FCP 128 vs TS 91 (TS stretches harder). blackIn=0.3 in=64 -> FCP 20 vs TS 0 (TS crushes shadows harder).",
      "refines_root_cause": "Sharpens the colour rule further. FAITHFUL in sRGB: fixed-weight LINEAR COMBINATIONS (ChannelMixer matrix dot) + per-channel GAMMA (Levels Gamma). DIVERGES (linear working space): any op that NORMALIZES/REMAPS relative to ENDPOINTS \u2014 Levels Black/White In (stretch (v-blackIn)/(whiteIn-blackIn)), Colorize Black/White mix, Brightness multiply+clip, Tint hard-light, HSV saturation. So the linear-working-space fix targets ENDPOINT-relative remaps + multiplies + luma-mix, NOT matrix dots or gamma curves.",
      "oracle_truth_caveat": "oracle_truth=gui (colour family). Matches the older channel-mixer.ts note (Black In=0.3 mean|\u0394|\u224812, White In=0.7 \u224834) and faithful PAELevels DIVERGED. The linear form that matches headless regresses the GUI gate; gate-blocked on the chain-level linear pipeline.",
      "note": "transfer.PAELevels (GAMMA only) stays VERIFIED (0.71 lvl) \u2014 the gamma curve is faithful; only the endpoint remap diverges. Split into two nodes to preserve that distinction."
    }
  ]
